In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening, eggs and milk; mix until smooth. In the bottom of 18 greased muffin cups, place 1 teaspoon of butter and 1 tablespoon brown sugar. Place in a 375 degrees F oven for 5 minutes. Arrange peaches in the muffin cups. fill each half full with batter. Bake at 375 degrees F for 25 minutes or until browned. Turn out of pans immediately.